Dozens of people are feared trapped after a heavy downpour triggered a mudslide in Sierra Leone’s capital, Freetown. The BBC’s Umaru Fofana has tweeted a picture of the mudslide: Hundreds feared buried in this #SierraLeonemudslide. Several houses completely covered People are sharing images of destruction left after heavy downpours in and near Sierra Leone’s capital, Freetown. The BBC’s Umaru Fofana says that a mudslide struck in early morning and dozens are feared buried. (BBC)